Loops

-- For
- we use range (inclusive interval) instead of i++
- if we want a range in reverse order backward we use downTo() or reversed()
- in case we want to step with n we use range.step(n)
- iterating over strings: we use IN operator
- until operator = exclusive interval
- collection.forEach { println(it) }
- collection.indices
- numeFunction@ = labels

-- IF
- ternary operator does not exist
- if statement returns a value
- Any == Object
- void == unit
- if returns a unit if does not have a type

-- When
- equivalent for switch
